<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90G2/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister Resident in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-29T17:00:00-04:00">June 29, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>14. Your No. 15, June 24, 11 a.m. Department accepts basis of negotiation
                            including reservation with respect to countries formerly included in
                            Ottoman Empire in Asia.</p>
                        <p>Draft treaty will be prepared here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>